            <fr:title text="Riesz-Fisher theorem">Riesz-Fisher theorem</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
            <fr:source-path>/Users/longie/forest/trees/FA-001G.tree</fr:source-path>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E \subset  \mathbb {R}^d]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001B.xml" addr="FA-001B" title="Measurable set">measurable set</fr:link> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p \in  [1, +\infty ]]]></fr:tex>. Then the <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001C.xml" addr="FA-001C" title="Space">space</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L^p(E)]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000F.xml" addr="FA-000F" title="Banach Space">Banach space</fr:link>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Moreover, if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p]]></fr:tex> is a positive integer, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p < +\infty ]]></fr:tex>, and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\{f_n\}_{n \in  \mathbb {N}}]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000X.xml" addr="FA-000X" title="Cauchy sequence">Cauchy sequence</fr:link> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[L^p(E)]]></fr:tex>, then there exist two functions <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f, h \in  L^p(E)]]></fr:tex> and a <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000R.xml" addr="FA-000R" title="Subsequence">subsequence</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f_{n_k}]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f_n]]></fr:tex> such that</fr:p>
            <fr:ol><fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[|f_{n_k}(x)| \leq  h(x)]]></fr:tex> <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001D.xml" addr="FA-001D" title="Almost everywhere">almost everywhere</fr:link> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex>,</fr:li>
<fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f_{n_k} \to  f]]></fr:tex> <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001D.xml" addr="FA-001D" title="Almost everywhere">almost everywhere</fr:link> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E]]></fr:tex>.</fr:li></fr:ol>
            <fr:p><fr:em>Note</fr:em>: The proof uses <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001E.xml" addr="FA-001E" title="Lebesgue's Dominated Convergence Theorem">Lebesgue's Dominated Convergence Theorem</fr:link>, <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001F.xml" addr="FA-001F" title="Monotone Convergence Theorem">Monotone Convergence Theorem</fr:link></fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
      <fr:backmatter />
    </fr:tree>
